[4
Date: Sat, 23 Mar 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail@org>
Source: Kyodo News, 14 Mar 2002 [edited
<http://home.kyodo.co.jp/all/display3para.jsp?an=20020315007&cate=>


The German government, aiming to recover consumer trust in meat
following the mad cow debacle, has launched a project to put a
computer chip in the ear of each animal to store production
information regarding the animals, government officials said
Wednesday. The system is being introduced on an experimental basis in
southern Bayern on cows, sheep and other animals. Information to be
stored in the chips includes each animal's birth date, where it was
born and raised, what types of meal it is being fed, and vaccination
information.

